race.comment: Wide open. GOD'S EYE (8) sat handy on debut and fought on well for fourth. Improver with the blinkers added and is among the main chances.  TENNESSEE BOUND (6) is a mare making her debut. By Written Tycoon from the stakes-winner Tennessee and well educated with four hit-outs, two this time in. Expected to measure up and is definitely one to watch for a strong push. ZOOM QUEEN (13) unraced 3yo filly who has had four jumpouts, the best being when she won at Cranbourne on September 22. Should be primed for a big debut. BIG VEE (7) three-year-old colt on debut. Placed latest hit-out at Hamilton over 1000m. Watch for any market confidence.
